@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #CCCCCC

title Registration Flow - Background CV Extraction

actor "Candidate" as Candidate
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "Auth Router\nPOST /auth/talent/register" as Auth
participant "Solvera Storage" as Storage
participant "CV Extraction Service\n(Background Task)" as CVService
database "PostgreSQL\ncandidate_info" as DB

note over Candidate, DB
  REGISTRATION WITH CV UPLOAD
  ========================
  Flow: Upload CV → Register → Background Extraction
end note

== Step 1: Registration Request ==

Candidate ->> FE: Fills registration form\n+ uploads CV file
FE ->> Auth: POST /auth/talent/register\n(form data + CV file)

== Step 2: Upload CV to Storage ==

note over Auth
  Validate CV file (PDF only, <10MB)
end note

Auth ->> Storage: Upload CV file
Storage -->> Auth: Return cv_url

== Step 3: Create User Account ==

Auth ->> DB: INSERT INTO users table
DB -->> Auth: User created

Auth ->> DB: INSERT INTO candidate_info\n(cv_url, created_at)
DB -->> Auth: candidate_info created

== Step 4: Return Success ==

Auth -->> FE: Registration successful\n(user_id, email, name)
FE -->> Candidate: "Registration successful!"

== Step 5: Background CV Extraction (Async) ==

note over Auth, CVService
  This happens AFTER registration returns
  No waiting - fire and forget
end note

Auth ->> CVService: asyncio.create_task(\nextract_and_save(cv_url, user_id))
activate CVService #LightYellow

== Step 6: Download and Process CV ==

CVService ->> Storage: GET cv_url\n(Download CV file)
Storage -->> CVService: CV file content (PDF)

CVService ->> CVService: extract_text_from_pdf()\n(Using pdfplumber)

note right
  Extract text from PDF:
  - Read all pages
  - Concatenate text
  - Return raw CV text
end note

== Step 7: Call Mistral API ==

CVService ->> Mistral: POST https://api.mistral.ai/v1/chat/completions

note right
  Prompt includes:
  - Structured extraction instructions
  - Raw CV text (max 15,000 chars)
  
  Response: JSON with extracted data
end note

Mistral -->> CVService: JSON response\n(profile, experience, education, skills, etc.)

CVService ->> CVService: Parse and validate JSON\ninto CVExtractedData

== Step 8: Save Extracted Data ==

CVService ->> DB: UPDATE candidate_info SET\ncv_extracted_profile = {...},\ncv_extracted_experience = [...],\ncv_extracted_education = [...],\ncv_extracted_skills = [...],\ncv_extraction_status = 'completed'

DB -->> CVService: Update success

deactivate CVService

note over Candidate
  RESULT:
  - User registered successfully
  - CV stored in database
  - Extracted data saved automatically
  - User can view profile later and see\n  auto-filled data
end note

@enduml
